  "text": "The pass-through HTTP filter implementation follows the established Envoy extension patterns found in the envoyproxy/envoy repository. The filter inherits from Http::StreamDecoderFilter (envoy/http/filter.h), which defines the core interface for HTTP decoder filters with methods decodeHeaders, decodeData, decodeTrailers, and setDecoderFilterCallbacks. The implementation is modeled after the pattern used in source/extensions/filters/http/common/pass_through_filter.h, which provides PassThroughDecoderFilter as a base implementation that returns Continue status for all operations. The filter factory and registration pattern is based on the NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory pattern as seen in source/extensions/filters/http/local_ratelimit/ and source/extensions/filters/http/router/ directories. The configuration class inherits from Common::FactoryBase (source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h) and uses google.protobuf.Empty as the configuration message type, similar to minimal filter configurations. The filter is registered using the LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY macro (source/extensions/filters/http/local_ratelimit/config.cc pattern) with the filter name 'envoy.filters.http.pass_through'. All key signatures and return types (FilterHeadersStatus::Continue, FilterDataStatus::Continue, FilterTrailersStatus::Continue) follow the established extension patterns in the codebase."
